This is a hibernate example, will use next technology: hibernate, spring

Task to do:
1, Basic CURD, for one table.*
2, POJO relationship: one-to-one, one-to-many, many-to-one, many-to-many.
3, Inherited relationship, table/class hierarchy, table/subclass, table/concrete class.*
4, First level cache, second level cache.
5, XML configuration and Annotation configuration.*
6, Execute native SQL.*
7, Make all HQL/SQL is not in java code.*
8, Research Tool, DB==>POJO,XML, XML==>DB,POJO.*
9, Criteria.*
10, Example.*
11, Dynamic HQL, using Freemarker.
12, FetchMode: DEFAULT, JOIN, SELECT.*
13, MatchMode: EXACT, START, END, ANYWHERE.*
14, Optimistic lock & Pessimistic lock.*
15, Lazy loading.*

If you want to run:
1, checkout out parent and run: 
    git clone git@github.com:bulain/parent.git
    mvn install
2, checkout out common and run: 
    git clone git@github.com:bulain/common.git
    mvn install
3, checkout out hibernate-demo:
    git clone git@github.com:bulain/hibernate-demo.git
    mvn eclipse:eclipse
